== 6...e6 · Wiesbaden variation ==
Black prepares to develop their dark-squared bishop to b4 where it stands uncontested thanks to White's move [[../../../|'''5. a4''']].

If White tries to recapture the c4 pawn immediately with 7. Nxc4 Black can strike back 7...c5 seizing the initiative.

The only move that preserves White's advantage is '''7. f3''', trying to play e4 on the next move. This threat cannot be stopped by Black, who ends up playing '''7...Bb4''' to keep his activity. The most common continuation is '''8. e4 Bxe4''' sacrificing the light-squared bishop in exchange for three pawns. The following exchanges are practically forced: '''9. fxe4 Nxe4 10. Bd2 Qxd4 11. Nxe4 Qxe4+ 12. Qe2 Bxd2+ 13. Kxd2 Qd5+ 14. Kc2''' and Black is up four pawns, but will inevitably lose the c4 pawn. 

