=== History ===
The Wiesbaden variation is named after the 1929 World Championship match between Alekhine and Bogoljubov. Bogoljubov entered the line in games three<ref>https://www.chessgames.com/perl/chessgame?gid=1012596</ref> and five<ref>https://www.chessgames.com/perl/chessgame?gid=1012597</ref> which took place in Wiesbaden. 


